{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:50:13.804118+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 73, "prompt_tokens": 4158, "total_tokens": 4231, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 18, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 2944}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "07cb16038de8456699b5dba8c805d742", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead81-8f1e-7540-94a8-b1515b5e1160-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C03_A01", "path": "README.md"}, "id": "call_d6105c9bbec248a29b8575fd", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 4158, "output_tokens": 73, "total_tokens": 4231, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 2944}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 18}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:50:14.867469+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:hI3NHu | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: dd8f230ebcee1ed2c87953be052ec8d2681c21fc)", "id": "lc_7a7ccf1a-a217-4a52-b6b4-79afcf33e832"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:hI3NHu | # vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | `vidpack` is a small Python CLI that runs FFmpeg using named profiles defined\n| MCP:hI3NHu | in `profiles.toml`. The goal is to avoid memorizing long ffmpeg flag strings\n| MCP:hI3NHu | for routine encoding jobs.\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | FFmpeg is **not** bundled. `vidpack` expects `ffmpeg` (and `ffprobe`, where\n| MCP:hI3NHu | relevant) to be available on `PATH`.\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | ## Install\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | ```\n| MCP:hI3NHu | pip install -e .\n| MCP:hI3NHu | ```\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | This registers the `vidpack` command.\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | ## Profiles\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | The default `profiles.toml` ships three profiles:\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | | Profile   | Container | Video codec | Audio codec | Notes                       |\n| MCP:hI3NHu | |-----------|-----------|-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|\n| MCP:hI3NHu | | `web`     | mp4       | libx264     | aac         | 720p, target bitrate 2 Mbps |\n| MCP:hI3NHu | | `archive` | mkv       | libx265     | flac        | source resolution, CRF 18   |\n| MCP:hI3NHu | | `gif`     | gif       | (palette)   | (none)      | 480p wide, 12 fps           |\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | Edit `profiles.toml` to customize or add profiles.\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | ## Usage\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | ```\n| MCP:hI3NHu | vidpack <profile> <input> [-o OUTPUT] [--dry-run]\n| MCP:hI3NHu | ```\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | If `-o` is omitted, the output filename is derived from the input by\n| MCP:hI3NHu | replacing the extension with the profile's container extension.\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | `--dry-run` prints the ffmpeg command vidpack would run, without executing it.\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | By default, vidpack will **not** overwrite an existing output file; it exits\n| MCP:hI3NHu | with an error. Delete the output manually or pass a different `-o`.\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | ## Examples\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | ```\n| MCP:hI3NHu | # Re-encode an mp4 for web at 720p\n| MCP:hI3NHu | vidpack web input.mov -o talk.mp4\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | # Lossless-ish archive copy\n| MCP:hI3NHu | vidpack archive input.mov\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | # Preview the ffmpeg command for the gif profile without running it\n| MCP:hI3NHu | vidpack gif clip.mp4 --dry-run\n| MCP:hI3NHu | ```\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | ## License\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | MIT", "id": "lc_992448d9-9e7e-44a9-b6bc-757135b76db9"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "77c6077e-91d7-45c6-abb7-9469c8521e72", "tool_call_id": "call_d6105c9bbec248a29b8575fd", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
