{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:51:21.838782+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:hI3NHu | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 79b42fb8b01da64a8ef6463122f5b79257277d8d)", "id": "lc_16eddb1a-b785-48ef-afeb-01efd6c9ee89"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:hI3NHu | from pathlib import Path\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | from vidpack import profiles, runner\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | def test_default_profiles_loaded():\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     all_p = profiles.load_all(Path(\"profiles.toml\"))\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     assert set(all_p.keys()) == {\"web\", \"archive\", \"gif\"}\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | def test_web_profile_shape():\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     p = profiles.load_profile(\"web\", Path(\"profiles.toml\"))\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     assert p[\"container\"] == \"mp4\"\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     assert p[\"video_codec\"] == \"libx264\"\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     assert p[\"audio_codec\"] == \"aac\"\n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | \n| MCP:hI3NHu | def test_build_command_web():\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     p = profiles.load_profile(\"web\", Path(\"profiles.toml\"))\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     cmd = runner.build_ffmpeg_command(p, Path(\"in.mov\"), Path(\"out.mp4\"))\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     assert cmd[0] == \"ffmpeg\"\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     assert \"libx264\" in cmd\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     assert \"aac\" in cmd\n| MCP:hI3NHu |     assert cmd[-1] == \"out.mp4\"", "id": "lc_3000c292-8070-4c2e-a33c-42bf47c72780"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "b74f2d71-30dd-4f2c-80c3-48ea64a5090e", "tool_call_id": "call_73aa3605c10241b7ac9e38ca", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:51:40.041992+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 584, "prompt_tokens": 13083, "total_tokens": 13667, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 287, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 12544}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "f7251b2c212a40de8941c7cd84f2667c", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead82-a8f0-7ed0-862f-aeec3de1bef3-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C03_A01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the detailed report, @BruceKZ. This is indeed a known limitation of the gif profile: it uses a single-pass palette generation (as noted in `profiles.toml`), which produces noticeably worse color quality than a proper two-pass palettegen/paletteuse pipeline.\n\nThe comment in `profiles.toml` already references this issue tracker, so this issue is the canonical tracking item for that improvement.\n\nA few notes:\n1. The quality difference you're seeing is expected with the current single-pass approach.\n2. Your older FFmpeg version (4.2.7) may include a known palettegen regression that could exacerbate the banding. Upgrading to FFmpeg ≥ 5.0 (or the 6.0 you initially mentioned) might improve results somewhat, even with single-pass.\n3. Switching to a two-pass palette generation would definitely improve GIF quality—this is a worthwhile enhancement.\n\nWe'll keep this issue open to track the two-pass palette improvement. If you're interested in contributing a PR, we'd be happy to review it. Otherwise, we'll prioritize it as time allows.\n\nThanks again for testing and reporting!"}, "id": "call_4ac814c847d943ef94a64511", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13083, "output_tokens": 584, "total_tokens": 13667, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 12544}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 287}}}}]}}}
